public interface TypeCanBeNativeCapable
extends TypeNativeObject

The TypeCanBeNativeCapable is the interface that represents a native type declaration of "can be native" classes and native wrapper classes (user defined and predefined).

Method Detail

wrapValue

CanBeNativeCapable wrapValue(java.lang.Object value)
Wraps (makes native capable) a "can be native" object with a native capable wrapper object.

For instance:

  • If value is a String instance, the returned object is a NativeString.
  • If value is a String[] instance, the returned object is a NativeStringArray.
  • If value is an Integer instance, the returned object is a NativeIntegerObject.
If value is null, returns null.

Parameters:
value - the "can be native" object to wrap.
Returns:
the native wrapper object or null.
